author: mvdb
msg: In using the feedparser API I've encountered a number of RSS feeds that are
missing the lenght attribute for enclosures. This causes feedparser to throw a
NPE. The standard does say that length is a required element, but in practice
Thanx Andrew McCall andrew.mccall at goroam.net

author: mvdb
msg: 've attached a patch that allows commons-feedparser to be built against jdom
1.0. I've changed all references to XPath to JDOMXPath. Also in AtomFeedParser
I've changed the call to new XMLOutputter("        ",  true) to a call to the no
argument constructor as the constructor being used is no longer available.
Patch supplied by Andrew McCall andrew.mccall at goroam.net
